Step 12: Add Customer Service security
Create:
customer-service/src/main/java/com/primecart/config/SecurityConfig.java
Use the Order Service security configuration as the base, with these authorization rules:
.authorizeHttpRequests(auth -> auth
    .requestMatchers(
        "/actuator/health/**",
        "/actuator/info",
        "/actuator/prometheus"
    ).permitAll()

    .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.GET, "/api/customers/me")
    .hasRole("PROFILE_READ")

    .requestMatchers(HttpMethod.PUT, "/api/customers/me")
    .hasRole("PROFILE_UPDATE")

    .anyRequest()
    .authenticated()
)
Keep the same JWT decoder configuration used by Order Service:
@Bean
JwtDecoder jwtDecoder(
        @Value("${spring.security.oauth2.resourceserver.jwt.issuer-uri}")
        String issuerUri,
        @Value("${primecart.security.jwt.audience}")
        String expectedAudience) {

    NimbusJwtDecoder decoder = NimbusJwtDecoder
        .withIssuerLocation(issuerUri)
        .build();

    OAuth2TokenValidator<Jwt> issuerValidator =
        JwtValidators.createDefaultWithIssuer(issuerUri);

    OAuth2TokenValidator<Jwt> audienceValidator =
        new AudienceValidator(expectedAudience);

    decoder.setJwtValidator(
        new DelegatingOAuth2TokenValidator<>(
            issuerValidator,
            audienceValidator
        )
    );

    return decoder;
}
Configure the resource server with the custom role converter:
.oauth2ResourceServer(oauth -> oauth.jwt(jwt -> jwt
    .decoder(jwtDecoder)
    .jwtAuthenticationConverter(
        new JwtAuthenticationConverter()
    )
));
